 about the `isTerminal` on the Properties object and why that's a problematic reflection. It raises questions about creating a `java.io.Console`. However, using `System.console()` seems better, and if it returns null, I could check via `assertThat(Properties.consoleIsTerminal()).isFalse`. I'm also considering tests; should the test class be public? When using Scala, the final class compiles as public without an access modifier. Alright, I need to compare that with a git diff.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_04c0dbe60f8759600169f52499a6a881a08a9baccaaf11f1e1\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9SSmZWDs8GR4k1Xm-_Omq1AVVwb2fPqjrK726_-09UjLkGwqF2IfSJ6O01DpQl7iTxauPTwrnAvbSRReKABT0m3-l79FqNrC0lu-F14F8eV-9Vt-BK71mPpiKa4iQTLebOpX6M_zPAWXZYef7eRlywrLK9n6CdQQac6wCSlvBWzNbVXElPxPwZO-ja3HgqSHqZa7iqknCJMue8xwOjjA0gP3Mp4JKQEtyBENUxxCmlZtj_ownvWseoV0jAcYbtkcrN8luzbvvHB5QxblFhXJSBm51BnIqi5FL8Fq_9xZviMCmsTznHLdlvFXXPObgtpZaje6B-8m0YUQkTPqUWvJpD9XcA-tNWcSqqozbAOWgdL0DqfM_oKn_FbX2XKUusVgxttGIPffCrPIMMXouIq47RuW0cTge0ggVl9Y7GbnPbEVUiAcd6LEzbw9fF_psFwrpRMUCS70irbrsKgTibCb6cK9z50Rh32EDNYRtK6rLw6qzpeBVP6JywK1gKbjandYAwudwjxXgJRUK1KZrFCZ38vV_456_LIWgSfbqK4SFkd6brKNJxSV_be4TjPIIx-GiKWR6--51cE_qePIbAY-rVsAuq7phfrwzbhtv4jderwH3-4oIAWbeK-YjrnOiD8pGRDwJebnsVxIHj-YJvTdvyJnPzaxej8vfDRkQOnS7UJBrw7e9aPpAXQFifzqR_smMNrr7wcaDUlAHYORRaAFWe8kSENvJN8LuWeeDbZ7JgbMoNLT5oZmycBqYTJ5LdLMdjydfHurcwDZKL8ZxLUdyhGnDYz2npeK7C2XIgFyidjIzv1crf3OyZ12aaitDqiJEXU_i8Mu5fknL6UEJyUoz7AcCr7UVY170M7hWvZJhuopQZwSWo4sl4SKdm-KaCUsh564NJfMKVxyuZHz2aL6Eldh_wD0vNINUg2my6s1Yf9wU15ML2WqmNrW3TFQ-F62Im2W0YvIruzfrTig1xkPtSLB56-QSHwKTZ5-2m09C7mJAuFH8hPAafCYgIAq1pamSTka8yb5VeCACYwycR3nZK0Q6fAz2wVmpddTPVjLoqpnrLGbma04aoCDQ7eaN5YkLQ5kVmbmwe3frlk4WTYTOvyyYu3Xuj3wJ21Cal8lzRHEKEXIK4kPVPvHG4R3BxPCk8-m0Kwsxk5RE06Ooi4-2lmV-USE76FOz1GdNcOyR4coem-_6sUm061RSrH1EC1ymzhaoJP7hGJME1oH5JF7-9RMgMKW8GOZmq5a1YlC4TkHyTtlt1pn41Jg-tIbkg2aC47UUE7P8bIbj0Rj1-ooFQ8S5xJXBAXpoEQy8mmo7kgaEV5t_NnJaq97tn5OgMc0Dl5L0N8ORKTTpELb6EaxQcaYNYtv3_